TITLE: The tragedy of Herschel Walker isn't over yet

The assumption that a Black football player whose celebrated symbolism in Georgia would be enough to split the Black vote thankfully went unrealized, but the reality that a number of White Georgians were willing to support Walker underscores the troubling questions ahead for a country mired in division and bracing for former President Donald Trump's bid for his old office in 2024.

TITLE: 'Avatar: The Way of Water' rekindles the wonder in a way that demands to be seen

Thirteen years later, braving much different theatrical tides, director James Cameron has done it again with "Avatar: The Way of Water," a state-of-the-art exercise that rekindles that sense of wonder and demands to be seen by anyone with lingering interest in watching movies in theaters.
